article.headline: Price scores 22, leads Eastern Washington past Idaho 87-79
article.description: — Ethan Price had 22 points in Eastern Washington's 87-79 victory over Idaho on Saturday night.
article.linkText: Price scores 22, leads Eastern Washington past Idaho 87-79
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. -- — Ethan Price had 22 points in Eastern Washington's 87-79 victory over Idaho on Saturday night. Price shot 8 for 13 from the floor (2 for 5 from 3-point range) and 4 of 5 from the free-throw line for the Eagles (16-8, 10-1 Big Sky Conference). Cedric Coward scored 15 points on 6-for-10 shooting, adding eight rebounds, three steals, and four blocks. Jake Kyman sank 4 of 5 from 3-point range and scored 14. The Vandals (9-15, 3-8) were led by EJ Neal with 20 points. Quinn Denker had 19 points and six assists. D'Angelo Minnis pitched in with 17 points and four assists. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
